{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d90f7a1e-388c-40f2-9bab-e389feb4040c","content":"There's no pipeline file in the current directory, so here's a general migration guide:\n\n### Key Changes\n\n1. **Replace `VSTest@3` with `DotNetCoreCLI@2` (or a plain `dotnet test` script step)**. Microsoft.Testing.Platform runs via `dotnet test` — there's no separate test adapter task needed.\n\n2. **Enable TRX output** with the `--logger` flag:\n   ```yaml\n   - task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n     displayName: Run tests\n     inputs:\n       command: test\n       projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n       arguments: >-\n         --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n         --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n         --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n   ```\n\n3. **Publish test results** (unchanged):\n   ```yaml\n   - task: PublishTestResults@2\n     condition: always()\n     inputs:\n       testResultsFormat: VSTest\n       testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n   ```\n\n4. **Publish code coverage** (unchanged):\n   ```yaml\n   - task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n     inputs:\n       summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n   ```\n   If you use the built-in Microsoft collector, the output is `.coverage`; for Cobertura/Coverlet, add `--collect \"XPlat Code Coverage\"` instead.\n\n5. **In your `.csproj`**, ensure you reference the new runner:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild\" Version=\"...\" />\n   ```\n   and optionally set `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` in a `Directory.Build.props` to opt all projects in.\n\n### Summary of what to drop\n- Remove the `VSTest@3` task entirely.\n- Remove any `vstest.console.exe` arguments or runsettings references that are VSTest-runner-specific.\n\nWould you like me to create a sample pipeline YAML file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"67dba6a2-ee99-4933-87dd-11ef8f5717d2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears to be empty. The user is asking a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their CI pipeline. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":590,"requestId":"67E4:2636C7:2AF180D:2F38317:69FD3463"},"id":"7cfe255c-f593-4f5a-85f6-a2f6c34c1e3c","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:55:12.189Z","parentId":"fc2c0f69-f896-4a2b-82be-d7ed0acbcc0b"}
